<task id="create-subject-scheme">
  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="steven_higgs" timestamp="20150617T115724+0300" comment="At some point, this was merged into &quot;Creating a Map&quot; and moved to the &quot;not_used&quot; folder."?>Create
    a Subject Scheme<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>DITA Maps<indexterm>creating a subject scheme</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>The procedure for creating a DITA subject scheme is similar with that for creating a
      map.</context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Go to menu <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol><image href="../../img/New16.png" id="image_b2w_qmq_sr"/>New</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> or click the <uicontrol><image href="../../img/New16.png"
              id="image_ftp_qmq_sr"/>New</uicontrol> toolbar button.</cmd>
        <stepresult>This action will open <xref keyref="wizard.new-document">the
              <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> wizard</xref>.</stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the <uicontrol>DITA Map - Subject Scheme</uicontrol> template.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
        <stepresult>A new tab with the new subject scheme document is added in <xref href="../topics/editing-dita-maps.dita#editing-dita-maps" format="dita">the
              <uicontrol>DITA Maps Manager</uicontrol> view</xref>.</stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Press the <uicontrol><image href="../../img/Save16.png" id="image_c13_4mq_sr"
            />Save</uicontrol> button on the toolbar of the <uicontrol>DITA Maps Manager</uicontrol>
          view.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>In the <uicontrol>Save As</uicontrol> dialog select a location and a file name for the
          map.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>